        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 6 at 1:27AM MDT by NWS Rapid City SD</headline>
        <description>At 126 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 3
miles west of Upton, or 26 miles southwest of Sundance, moving
northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Upton and Inyan Kara Mountain.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
